cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB 

The paper discusses the implementation of author identifiers in scholarly repositories, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it directly deals with the management and organization of scholarly repositories. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it involves the retrieval and analysis of scholarly information. cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still relevant as they deal with issues related to privacy and security in the management of scholarly information. cs.DB (Databases) is also relevant as it deals with the organization and management of large datasets, which is relevant to the implementation of author identifiers in scholarly repositories.
